# Auto dev workflow (test on latest)

The user wants agents on **latest main**, **one Metro window**, and **git commits for backtracking** — not a new Metro popup on every subagent task.

## Which script to run

| Situation | Script | Metro |
|-----------|--------|-------|
| Metro down, first connect of the day, adb broken | `flip-dev.bat` | Starts **one** window if `/status` not healthy |
| Metro stuck, stale cache, native dep change | `flip-dev-restart.bat` | Kills 8081, then **one** new window |
| JS/icon tweak, Metro already running | `flip-reload.bat` or hot-reload on device | **No** recycle |
| USB replug, app crashed, Metro already up | `flip-connect.bat` | **No** recycle |
| Native Android rebuild | `npm run android:dev` | Metro separate |

**Agents:** do **not** run `flip-dev.bat` or `dev:connect:restart` for routine JS edits when Metro is already healthy. Commit + push; user hot-reloads or runs `flip-reload.bat`. Use git history to backtrack mistakes.

`flip-dev.bat` reuses Metro when `http://127.0.0.1:8081/status` returns `packager-status:running` — it does **not** open another Metro window.

## Before testing or saying "please test"

1. **Sync** — from the Flip repo root:
   ```bash
   git pull origin main
   ```
   Report whether new commits were pulled. `flip-dev.bat` pulls automatically; lightweight scripts do not.

2. **Connect device** — only when you need the user to validate on hardware:
   - Metro already up: `flip-reload.bat` (JS reload) or `flip-connect.bat` (adb + relaunch)
   - Metro down or unsure: `flip-dev.bat` once
   - Never run `npm run start:clear` in a **new** window if Metro is already healthy — that stacks windows

3. **Windows** — if `npm` fails under PowerShell execution policy, use `npm.cmd`.

## Pair with other Flip rules

- **[dev-permissions.mdc](dev-permissions.mdc)** — use `required_permissions: ["all"]` for flip-dev, flip-connect, adb, Metro, git remote.
- **[auto-permissions.mdc](auto-permissions.mdc)** — request `git_write`, `network` / `full_network`, and `all` on the first attempt when pulling, installing, or connecting; do not stop to ask for routine approval.
- **[auto-push-progress.mdc](auto-push-progress.mdc)** — after meaningful work, commit and push unless the user says not to; then pull again before the next test cycle if others may have merged.

## After dependency or native changes

If `package.json`, lockfile, or native modules changed on pull, run `npm install` (or `npm.cmd install` on Windows) before connecting. For Android native changes, follow existing project scripts (`android:prebuild`, `android:dev`, etc.) and use `flip-dev-restart.bat` afterward.
